						<summary>

						<p>Nandi-pillar set up in fron of the Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Vīra Bukkarāya.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1275, Ānanda, (current), Kārttīka śu. 1, Thursday,</hi> corresponding to 1354 A.D. However, the week day is Saturday.</p>						

						<p>It registers the grant of the village in Kaṁnāḍu for worship of the god Saṅgamēśvaradēva to the religious teacher Aghōraśivāchārya, by Tipparāju son of Saṁgarāju. Further it also mentions about the erection of Nandi-staṁbha.</p>						

						</summary>
